National Express Biggest Owner May Back Elliott, Observer Says

-- B y   C a r o l i n e   A l e x a n d e r
-- 
2011-04-03T07:14:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-03/national-express-biggest-owner-may-back-elliott-observer-says.html
National Express Group Plc (NEX) ’s biggest
shareholder Jorge Cosmen may back Elliott Advisors, the British
arm of U.S. hedge-fund firm Elliott Associates LP, in seeking a
boardroom shake-up and possibly a breakup, the Observer
newspaper  said , without saying where it got the information.  Cosmen, who owns 20 percent of the company, wasn’t
available for comment, according to the report.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Caroline Alexander in London at 
